# 9a455564ce874041b26f511ee59f006a
#: ../../home/kovid/work/calibre/manual/edit.rst:5
msgid "Editing E-books"
msgstr "Éditer des E-books"

# 2c6b9f9f8903471da6a18c625430d4df
#: ../../home/kovid/work/calibre/manual/edit.rst:7
msgid ""
"|app| has an integrated e-book editor that can be used to edit books in the "
"EPUB and AZW3 (Kindle) formats. The editor shows you the HTML and CSS that "
"is used internally inside the book files, with a live preview that updates "
"as you make changes. It also contains various automated tools to perform "
"common cleanup and fixing tasks."
msgstr "|app| a un éditeur d'e-book intégré qui peut être utilisé pour éditer des livres aux formats EPUB et AZW3 (Kindle). L'éditeur vous montre l'HTML et le CSS qui sont utilisés à l'intérieur des fichiers livre, avec une prévisualisation direct qui se met à jour au fur et à mesure que vous faites des changements. Il contient aussi divers outils automatisés pour effectuer un nettoyage usuel et des tâches de réparation. "

# e8e715fa6f2d4ccdae3cf984a70cdbc3
#: ../../home/kovid/work/calibre/manual/edit.rst:13
msgid ""
"You can use this editor by right clicking on any book in |app| and selecting"
" :guilabel:`Edit book`."
msgstr "Vous pouvez utiliser cet éditeur en faisant un clic droit sur n'importe quel livre dans |app| et en sélectionnant guilabel:`Editer le livre`."

# 1eee3cd5bc4a42a88b9a1b0b1209410c
#: ../../home/kovid/work/calibre/manual/edit.rst:0
msgid "Contents"
msgstr "Contenu"

# d40c3aa864fa4e1a99ca5182065efc03
#: ../../home/kovid/work/calibre/manual/edit.rst:27
msgid "Basic workflow"
msgstr "Fonctionnement de base"

# 6733c725dea84a10ae80fd131c3b626a
#: ../../home/kovid/work/calibre/manual/edit.rst:29
msgid ""
"When you first open a book with the Edit book tool, you will be presented "
"with a list of files on the left. These are the individual HTML files, "
"stylesheets, images, etc. that make up the content of the book. Simply "
"double click on a file to start editing it. Note that if you want to do "
"anything more sophisticated than making a few small tweaks, you will need to"
" know `HTML Tutorial <http://html.net/tutorials/html/>`_ and `CSS Tutorial "
"<http://html.net/tutorials/css/>`_."
msgstr "Quand vous ouvrez un livre la première fois avec l'outil d'édition de livre, vous serez en présence d'une liste de fichiers sur la gauche. Ceux-ci sont les fichiers HTML individuels, les feuilles de style, les images, etc. qui forment le contenu du livre. Double cliquez simplement sur un fichier pour démarrer son édition. Notez que si vous voulez faire quelque chose de plus sophistiqué que de faire quelques petits ajustements, vous aurez besoin de connaître `le Tutoriel HTML <http://html.net/tutorials/html/>`_ et `le Tutoriel CSS <http://html.net/tutorials/css/>`_."

# 4a64d63a761c4458a735e05055010729
#: ../../home/kovid/work/calibre/manual/edit.rst:37
msgid ""
"As you make changes to the HTML or CSS in the editor, the changes will be "
"previewed, live, in the preview panel to the right. When you are happy with "
"how the changes you have made look, click the Save button or use "
":guilabel:`File->Save` to save your changes into the ebook."
msgstr "Au fur et à mesure que vous faites des changements à l'HTML ou au CSS dans l'éditeur, les changements seront prévisualisés, en direct, dans le panneau de prévisualisation à gauche. Quand vous êtes content avec l'apparence des changements que vous avez fait, cliquez sur le bouton Enregistrer ou utilisez :guilabel:`Fichier->Enregistrer` pour sauvegarder vos changements dans le livre."

# 7fb0921d2ab34e27bf76aeaacf07907c
#: ../../home/kovid/work/calibre/manual/edit.rst:42
msgid ""
"One useful feature is :guilabel:`Checkpoints`. Before you embark on some "
"ambitious set of edits, you can create a checkpoint. The checkpoint will "
"preserve the current state of your book, then if in the future you decide "
"you dont like the changes you have made to you can go back to the state when"
" you created the checkpoint. To create a checkpoint, use "
":guilabel:`Edit->Create checkpoint`. Checkpoints will also be automatically "
"created for you whenever you run any automated tool like global search and "
"replace. The checkpointing functionality is in addition to the normal "
"Undo/redo mechanism when editing individual files. Checkpoints are useful "
"for when changes are spread over multiple files in the book."
msgstr "Une caractéristique intéressante est :guilabel:`Points de contrôle`. Avant de vous embarquer dans un ensemble ambitieux d'éditions, vous pouvez créer un point de contrôle. Le point de contrôle préservera l'état actuel de votre livre, dès lors si dans le futur vous décidez que vous n'appréciez pas les changements que vous lui avez fait vous pouvez revenir à l'état au moment où vous avez créer le point de contrôle. Pour créer unn point de contrôle, utilisez :guilabel:`Editer->Créer un point de contrôle`. Les points de contrôle seront aussi créés automatiquement pour vous au moment où vous exécutez n'importe quel outil automatisé comme la recherche globale et remplacer. La fonctionnalité point de contrôle est en complément au mécanisme normal Annuler/Restaurer lors de l'édition de fichiers individuels. Les points de contrôle vous sont utiles quand les changements sont disséminés sur de multiples fichiers dans le livre."

# 4b45334f58884797977b5a5571dd178d
#: ../../home/kovid/work/calibre/manual/edit.rst:53
msgid ""
"That is the basic work flow for editing books -- Open a file, make changes, "
"preview and save. The rest of this manual will discuss the various tools and"
" features present to allow you to perform specific tasks efficiently."
msgstr "C'est le flux de travail basique pour l'édition de livres -- Ouvrir un fichier, faire des changements, prévisualiser et sauver. Le reste de ce manuel traitera des divers outils et caractéristiques présents pour vous permettre d'exécuter efficacement des tâches spécifiques."

# f0fb339f9fe24c3d9027fb64bfbd63b7
#: ../../home/kovid/work/calibre/manual/edit.rst:58
msgid "The Files Browser"
msgstr "Le navigateur de fichiers"

# 3f6c6552eaba49138c8ee8c8ccb02eca
#: ../../home/kovid/work/calibre/manual/edit.rst:64
msgid ""
"The :guilabel:`Files Browser` gives you an overview of the various files "
"inside the book you are editing. The files are arranged by category, with "
"text (HTML) files at the top, followed by stylesheet (CSS) files, images and"
" so on. Simply double click on a file to start editing it. Editing is "
"supported for HTML, CSS and image files. The order of text files is the same"
" order that they would be displayed in, if you were reading the book. All "
"other files are arranged alphabetically."
msgstr "Le :guilabel:`Navigateur de Fichiers` vous donne un aperçu des différents fichiers à l'intérieur du livre que vous êtes occupé à éditer. Les fichiers sont arrangés par catégories, avec les fichiers texte (HTML) au sommet, suivis par les fichiers de feuilles de style (CSS), les images et ainsi de suite. Double cliquez simplement sur un fichier pour en commencer l'édition. L'édition est supportée pour le HTML, le CSS et les fichiers images. L'ordre des fichiers texte est le même ordre que celui dans lequel ils devraient être affichés, si vous êtes occupé de lire le livre. Tous les autres fichiers sont arrangés alphabétiquement."

# 98a7044f0f5e463fa35f03cc4065bcfd
#: ../../home/kovid/work/calibre/manual/edit.rst:72
msgid ""
"By hovering your mouse over an entry, you can see its size, and also, at the"
" bottom of the screen, the full path to the file inside the book. Note that "
"files inside ebooks are compressed, so the size of the final book is not the"
" sum of the individual file sizes."
msgstr "En passant votre souris sur une entrée, vous pouvez voir sa taille, et aussi, au bas de l'écran, le chemin complet au fichier à l'intérieur du livre. Notez que les fichiers à l'intérieurs des ebooks sont compressés, aussi la taille du livre final n'est pas la somme des tailles des fichiers individuels."

# baeb871e39144fb6aa78d850330bb094
#: ../../home/kovid/work/calibre/manual/edit.rst:77
msgid ""
"Many files have special meaning, in the book. These will typically have an "
"icon next to their names, indicating the special meaning. For example, in "
"the picture to the left, you can see that the files "
":guilabel:`cover_image.jpg` and :guilabel:`titlepage.xhtml` have the icon of"
" a cover next to them, this indicates they are the book cover image and "
"titlepage. Similarly, the :guilabel:`content.opf` file has a metadata icon "
"next to it, indicating the book metadata is present in it and the the "
":guilabel:`toc.ncx` file has a T icon next to it, indicating it is the Table"
" of Contents."
msgstr "Beaucoup de fichiers ont une signification spéciale. Ceux-ci auront généralement une icône à la suite de leurs noms, indiquant leur signification spéciale. Par exemple, dans l'image sur la gauche, vous pouvez voir que les fichiers :guilabel:`cover_image.jpg` et :guilabel:`titlepage.xhtml` ont l'icône d'une couverture à leur suite, ceci indique qu'ils sont l'image de couverture du livre et la page de titre. Similairement, le fichier :guilabel:`content.opf` à une icône métadonnée à sa suite, indiquant que les métadonnées du livre s'y trouvent et le fichier :guilabel:`toc.ncx` à une icône T à sa suite, indiquant que c'est la Table des Matières."

# 394c1eb4e53f4088a1cc372cc6259fde
#: ../../home/kovid/work/calibre/manual/edit.rst:86
msgid ""
"You can perform many actions on individual files, by right clicking them."
msgstr "Vous pouvez effectuer beaucoup d'actions sur les fichiers individuels, en faisant un clic droit sur ceux-ci."

# 9ba7e8d813b54752bd8f545186f3e0b7
#: ../../home/kovid/work/calibre/manual/edit.rst:89
msgid "Renaming files"
msgstr "Renommer les fichiers"

# 78007fc903f642708fda011eabb72aa2
#: ../../home/kovid/work/calibre/manual/edit.rst:91
msgid ""
"You can rename an individual file by right clicking it and selecting "
":guilabel:`Rename`. Renaming a file automatically updates all links and "
"references to it throughout the book. So all you have to do is provide the "
"new name, |app| will take care of the rest."
msgstr "Vous pouvez renommer un fichier individuel en y faisant un clic droit et en sélectionnant :guilabel:`Renommer`. Renommer un fichier met à jour automatiquement les liens et les références à celui-ci tout au long du livre. Donc tout ce que vous avez à faire est de fournir un nouveau nom, |app| prendra soin du reste."

# 3f23cf8f0f2a459ea64ba82c0bcf9c38
#: ../../home/kovid/work/calibre/manual/edit.rst:96
msgid ""
"You can also bulk rename many files at once. This is useful if you want the "
"files to have some simple name pattern. For example you might want to rename"
" all the HTML files to have names Chapter-1.html, Chapter-2.html and so on. "
"Select the files you want bulk renamed by holding down the Shift or Ctrl key"
" and clicking the files. Then right click and select :guilabel:`Bulk "
"rename`. Enter a prefix and what number you would like the automatic "
"numbering to start at, click OK and you are done."
msgstr "Vous pouvez également renommer par lot beaucoup de fichiers en une fois. C'est utile si vous voulez que les fichiers aient un certain modèle de nom élémentaire. Par exemple, vous pourriez vouloir renommer tous les fichiers HTML pour avoir des noms Chapitre-1.html, Chapitre-2.html et ainsi de suite. Sélectionnez les fichiers que vous voulez renommer en lot en maintenant la touche SHIFT ou la touche CTRL et en cliquant sur les fichiers. Puis clic droit et sélectionner :guilabel:`Renommer par lot`. Écrivez un préfixe et à quel nombre vous voudriez que la numérotation automatique commence, Cliquez OK et vous avez fini."

# 0b0ce03a2fcf40ecbcba4555897d734e
#: ../../home/kovid/work/calibre/manual/edit.rst:105
msgid "Merging files"
msgstr "Fusionner des fichiers "

# 874bf11d2a0b40d9afe9453e35e676be
#: ../../home/kovid/work/calibre/manual/edit.rst:107
msgid ""
"Sometimes, you may want to merge two HTML files or two CSS files together. "
"It can sometimes be useful to have everything in a single file. Be wary, "
"though, putting a lot of content into a single file will cause performance "
"problems when viewing the book in a typical ebook reader."
msgstr "Parfois, vous pouvez vouloir fusionner deux fichiers HTML ou deux fichiers CSS ensemble. Il peut parfois être utile d'avoir tout dans un fichier unique. Soyez attentif, toutefois, que mettre beaucoup de contenu dans un fichier unique pose des problèmes de performance lorsque vous visualisez le livre dans un lecteur d'ebook spécifique."

# db588028e56440999e5530bccbb83265
#: ../../home/kovid/work/calibre/manual/edit.rst:112
msgid ""
"To merge multiple files together, select them by holding the Ctrl key and "
"clicking on them (make sure you only select files of one type, either all "
"HTML files or all CSS files and so on). Then right click and select merge. "
"That's all, |app| will merge the files, automatically taking care of "
"migrating all links and references to the merged files. Note that merging "
"files can sometimes cause text styling to change, since the individual files"
" could have used different stylesheets."
msgstr "Pour fusionner de multiples fichiers ensemble, sélectionnez les en maintenant enfoncée la touche CTRL (Assurez vous de ne sélectionner des fichiers que d'un type, soit tous les fichiers HTML ou tous les fichers CSS et ainsi de suite). Faire alors un clic droit et sélectionner Fusionner. C'est tout. |app| fusionnera les fichiers, prendra automatiquement soin de faire la migration de tous les liens et références aux fichiers fusionnés. Notez que fusionner des fichiers peut parfois entraîner un changement du style de texte, puisque les fichiers individuels pourraient utiliser différentes feuilles de style. "

# ed1ca0497a2d4230a9fdfcdbcbe2b9ab
#: ../../home/kovid/work/calibre/manual/edit.rst:121
msgid "Changing text file order"
msgstr "Ordre de fichier texte changeant"

# bcbc244e1073412ea787bb0d62a2447d
#: ../../home/kovid/work/calibre/manual/edit.rst:123
msgid ""
"You can re-arrange the order in which text (HTML) files are opened when "
"reading the book by simply dragging and dropping them in the Files browser. "
"For the technically inclined, this is called re-ordering the book spine. "
"Note that you have to drop the items *between* other items, not on top of "
"them, this can be a little fiddly until you get used to it."
msgstr "Vous pouvez ré-arranger l'ordre dans lequel les fichiers texte (HTML) sont ouvert lors de la lecture du livre en effectuant simplement un glisser-déposer de ceux-ci dans le Navigateur de Fichiers. Techniquement, ceci s'appelle un réarrangement de la structure organisationnelle du livre. Notez que vous devez déposer les éléments \"entre\" d'autres articles, pas au dessus de ceux-ci, ceci peut être un peu délicat jusqu'à ce que vous vous y habituiez."

# a6e187ecf5584dafb1b2b224c0c0e40b
#: ../../home/kovid/work/calibre/manual/edit.rst:130
msgid "Marking the cover"
msgstr "Marquage de la couverture"

# c918ff38fc1c4ee3bd2f45af8e5652a9
#: ../../home/kovid/work/calibre/manual/edit.rst:132
msgid ""
"E-books typically have a cover image. This image is indicated in the Files "
"Browser by the icon of a brown book next to the image name. If you want to "
"designate some other image as the cover, you can do so by right clicking on "
"the file and choosing :guilabel:`Mark as cover`."
msgstr "Les livres numériques ont normalement une image de couverture. Cette image est signifiée dans le Navigateur de Fichiers pat l'icône d'un livre brun suivant le nom de l'image. Si vous voulez désigner quel qu’autre image comme couverture, vous pouvez faire cela en faisant un clic droit sur le fichier et en choisissant :guillabel:`Marquer comme image de couverture`."

# 82ad2b865c4447c39018647fe084aff9
#: ../../home/kovid/work/calibre/manual/edit.rst:137
msgid ""
"In addition, EPUB files has the concept of a *titlepage*. A title page is a "
"HTML file that acts as the title page/cover for th book. You can mark an "
"HTML file as the titlepage when editing EPUBs by right-clicking. Be careful "
"that the file you mark contains only the cover information. If it contains "
"other content, such as the first chapter, then that content will be lost if "
"the user ever converts the EPUB file in |app| to another format. This is "
"because when converting, |app| assumes that the marked title page contains "
"only the cover and no other content."
msgstr "En complément, les fichiers EPUB ont le concept de \"page de titre\". Une page de titre est un fichier HTML qui agit comme une page de titre/couverture pour le livre. Vous pouvez indiquez un fichier HTML comme page de titre lors de l'édition des EPUBs en faisant un clic droit. Assurez-vous que le fichier que vous désignez contient uniquement une information de couverture. S'il contient une autre information, comme le premier chapitre, alors le contenu sera perdu si jamais l'utilisateur convertit l'EPUB dans |app| à un autre format. C'est parce que lors de la conversion, |app| assume que la page de titre indiquée contient uniquement la couverture et pas d'autre contenu."

# 1391d4cf28904d8f9d62d4e64626a743
#: ../../home/kovid/work/calibre/manual/edit.rst:147
msgid "Deleting files"
msgstr "Suppression des fichiers"

# 451f019505ad42ffb2cb0ac700df1c73
#: ../../home/kovid/work/calibre/manual/edit.rst:149
msgid ""
"You can delete files by either right clicking on them or by selecting them "
"and pressing the Delete key. Deleting a file removes all references to the "
"file from the OPF file, saving you that chore. However, references in other "
"places are not removed, you can use the Check Book tool to easily find and "
"remove/replace them."
msgstr "Vous pouvez supprimer des fichiers soit en faisant un clic droit sur ceux-ci, soit en appuyant sur la touche Supprimer. Supprimer un fichier retire toutes les références au fichier du fichier OPF, en enregistrant cette tâche. Cependant, les références dans les autres emplacements ne sont pas retirées, vous pouvez utiliser l'outil de Vérification de Livre pour facilement les trouver et les les supprimer/remplacer."

# e132455708a94e0da4b52a9cba54dd04
#: ../../home/kovid/work/calibre/manual/edit.rst:156
msgid "Export of files"
msgstr "Export de fichiers"

# 6f17565a41b74905b6dc386c401d5dd7
#: ../../home/kovid/work/calibre/manual/edit.rst:158
msgid ""
"You can export a file from inside the book to somewhere else on your "
"computer. This is useful if you want to work on the file in isolation, with "
"specialised tools. To do this, simply right click on the file and choose "
":guilabel:`Export`."
msgstr "Vous pouvez exporter un fichier depuis l'intérieur du livre vers quelque part d'autre sur votre ordinateur. Ceci est utile si vous voulez travailler sur le fichier en isolation, avec des outils spécialisés. Pour faire ceci faire simplement un clic droit sur le fichier et choisissez :guillabel:`Exporter`."

# 3773a84720f7414ba6dcfaf6e62e332d
#: ../../home/kovid/work/calibre/manual/edit.rst:163
msgid ""
"Once you are done working on the exported file, you can re-import it into "
"the book, by right clicking on the file again and choosing "
":guilabel:`Replace with file...` which will allow you to replace the file in"
" the book with the previously exported file."
msgstr "Une fois que vous avez fini de travailler sur le fichier exporté, vous pouvez le ré-importer dans le livre, en faisant à nouveau un clic droit sur le fichier dans le livre et en choisissant :guilabel:`Remplacer avec le fichier...` qui vous permet de le fichier dans le livre avec le fichier précédemment exporté."

# 664dd0eb52344426a5d6f06dfd0614b7
#: ../../home/kovid/work/calibre/manual/edit.rst:169
msgid "Adding new images/fonts/etc. or creating new blank files"
msgstr "Ajout de nouvelles images/polices/etc. ou création de nouveaux fichiers vides"

# 72e673191cf74e9b8c7ed548b803684e
#: ../../home/kovid/work/calibre/manual/edit.rst:171
msgid ""
"You can add a new image, font, stylesheet, etc. from your computer into the "
"book by clicking :guilabel:`File->New file`. This lets you either import a "
"file by clicking the :guilabel:`Import resource file` button or create a new"
" blank html file or stylesheet by simply entering the file name into the box"
" for the new file."
msgstr "Vous pouvez ajouter une nouvelle image, police, feuille de style depuis votre ordinateur dans le livre en cliquant :guilabel:`Fichier->Nouveau fichier`. Ceci vous permet soit d'importer un fichier en cliquant sur le bouton :`Importer un fichier de ressources` ou de créer un html ou une feuille de style vide en écrivant simplement le nom du fichier dans la case pour le nouveau fichier."

# 2a3d960523654cc2a538a1ded6fd622d
#: ../../home/kovid/work/calibre/manual/edit.rst:176
msgid ""
"You can also import multiple files into the book at once using File->Import "
"files into book."
msgstr "Vous pouvez aussi importer de multiples fichiers dans le livre en une fois en utilisant Fichier->Importer des fichiers dans le livre."

# f9d2615f546f473480adb4484e5ba147
#: ../../home/kovid/work/calibre/manual/edit.rst:180
msgid "Replacing files"
msgstr "Remplacement des fichiers"

# d6c4d7121c044ad0972ffcdb709ee365
#: ../../home/kovid/work/calibre/manual/edit.rst:182
msgid ""
"You can easily replace existing files int he book, by right clicking on the "
"file and choosing replace. This will automatically update all links and "
"references, in case the replacement file has a different name than the file "
"being replaced."
msgstr "Vous pouvez facilement remplacer des fichiers dans le livre en faisant un clic droit sur le fichier et en choisissant remplacer. Ceci mettra automatiquement tous les liens et ressources à jour, dans le cas où le fichier de remplacement a un nom différent que le fichier en cours de remplacement."

# 75b00aadee224a7499dcc2b334ec2fb6
#: ../../home/kovid/work/calibre/manual/edit.rst:188
msgid "Linking stylesheets to HTML files efficiently"
msgstr "Lier des feuilles de style aux fichiers HTML efficacement"

# cd1030ceeec04483881e70fdc8ed8074
#: ../../home/kovid/work/calibre/manual/edit.rst:190
msgid ""
"As a convenience, you can select multiple HTML files in the Files Browser, "
"right click and choose Link stylesheets to have |app| automatically insert "
"the <link> tags for those stylesheets into all the selected HTML files."
msgstr "Par commodité, vous pouvez sélectionner de multiples HTML dans le Navigateur de Fichiers, faire un clic droit et choisir Lier les feuilles de style pour que |app| insère automatiquement les balises <link> pour ces feuilles de style dans tous les fichiers HTML sélectionnés."

# 13abcf18e9cc41d0913b676d87288973
#: ../../home/kovid/work/calibre/manual/edit.rst:200
msgid "Search & Replace"
msgstr "Rechercher Et Remplacer"

# 385a5ed21b3041a28a24daedbb62b256
#: ../../home/kovid/work/calibre/manual/edit.rst:202
msgid ""
"Edit Book has a very powerful search and replace interface that allows you "
"to search and replace text in the current file, across all files and even in"
" a marked region of the current file. You can search using a normal search "
"or using regular expressions. To learn how to use regular expressions for "
"advanced searching, see :ref:`regexptutorial`."
msgstr "Editer un livre possède une très puissante interface rechercher et remplacer qui vous permet de rechercher et remplacer du texte dans le fichier courant, à travers tous les fichiers et même dans une région marquée du fichier courant. Vous pouvez rechercher en utilisant une recherche normale ou en utilisant des expressions régulières. Pour apprendre comment utiliser des expressions régulières pour des recherches avancées, voir  :ref:`regexptutorial`."

# 5a4f76e43d37499da492b4fa252ce7c1
#: ../../home/kovid/work/calibre/manual/edit.rst:212
msgid ""
"Start the search and replace via the :guilabel:`Search->Find/replace` menu "
"entry (you must be editing an HTML or CSS file)."
msgstr "Démarrer le Rechercher et Remplacer via l'entrée de menu :guilabel:`Rechercher->Rechercher/Remplacer` (vous devez être occupé à éditer un fichier HTML ou CSS)."

# fab6cbb986fa44c4972651b11eabf9f1
#: ../../home/kovid/work/calibre/manual/edit.rst:215
msgid ""
"Type the text you want to find into the Find box and its replacement into "
"the Replace box. You can the click the appropriate buttons to Find the next "
"match, replace the current match and replace all matches."
msgstr "Taper le texte que vous voulez trouver dans la case Chercher et sont remplacement dans la case Remplacer. Vous pouvez cliquer les boutons appropriés pour trouver la correspondance suivante, remplacer la correspondance actuelle et remplacer toutes les correspondances."

# 11e66851da034fcba4c3e7407714eeef
#: ../../home/kovid/work/calibre/manual/edit.rst:219
msgid ""
"Using the drop downs at the bottom of the box, you can have the search "
"operate over the current file, all text files, all style files or all files."
" You can also choose the search mode to be a normal (string) search or a "
"regular expression search."
msgstr "En utilisant les menus déroulants en bas de la boîte de dialogue, vous pouvez opérer la recherche sur le fichier courant, tous les fichiers textes, tous les fichiers de style ou tous les fichiers. Vous pouvez aussi choisir le mode de recherche à être une recherche normale (chaîne) ou une recherche par expression régulière."

# 20cb2a637cfb4ac7be60052873426375
#: ../../home/kovid/work/calibre/manual/edit.rst:224
msgid ""
"You can count all the matches for a search expression via "
":guilabel:`Search->Count all`. The count will run over whatever "
"files/regions you have selected in the dropdown box."
msgstr "Vous pouvez compter toutes les correspondances pour une expression de recherche via :guilabel:`Rechercher->Tout compter`. Le comptage s'effectuera sur n'importe quels fichiers/régions que vous avez sélectionnés dans les menus déroulants."

# 10fa0cbf45654084af53941d3188ec8c
#: ../../home/kovid/work/calibre/manual/edit.rst:228
msgid ""
"You can also go to a specific line in the currently open editor via "
":guilabel:`Search->Go to line`."
msgstr "Vous pouvez aussi vous rendre à une ligne spécifique dans l'éditeur actuellement ouvert via :guilabel:`Rechercher->Aller à la ligne`."

# e26b209683fc4e50bba21779ca475616
#: ../../home/kovid/work/calibre/manual/edit.rst:232
msgid ""
"Remember, to harness the full power of search and replace, you will need to "
"use regular expressions. See :ref:`regexptutorial`."
msgstr "Rappelez-vous, pour vous armer de toute la puissance de la recherche et du remplacement, vous aurez besoin d'utiliser des expressions régulières. Voir : référence :ref:`regexptutorial`."

# 9b28ed3c77e14395811b7ec13005e1b8
#: ../../home/kovid/work/calibre/manual/edit.rst:236
msgid "Saved searches"
msgstr "Recherches sauvegardées"

# aa6beec941b44dd5ac9e52391d4c9885
#: ../../home/kovid/work/calibre/manual/edit.rst:238
msgid ""
"You can save frequently used search/replace expressions and reuse them "
"multiple times. To save a search simply right click in the Find box and "
"select :guilabel:`Save current search`."
msgstr "Vous pouvez sauvez les expressions rechercher/remplacer fréquemment utilisées et les réutilisés de multiples fois. Pour sauver une recherche faites simplement un clic droit dans la case de recherche et sélectionner :guilabel:`Sauvegarder la recherche actuelle`."

# 58f587f78551460f9649281953fcfd8b
#: ../../home/kovid/work/calibre/manual/edit.rst:241
msgid ""
"You can bring up the dialog of saved searches via :guilabel:`Search->Saved "
"Searches`. This will present you with a list of search and replace "
"expressions that you can apply. You can even select multiple entries in the "
"list by holding down the Ctrl Key while clicking so as to run multiple "
"search and replace expressions in a single operation."
msgstr ""

# c5c66a55e50f4c3882d223e08951b059
#: ../../home/kovid/work/calibre/manual/edit.rst:248
msgid "Automated tools"
msgstr "Outils automatisés"

# a7520d3808e8406f89c3fce2a55931d3
#: ../../home/kovid/work/calibre/manual/edit.rst:250
msgid ""
"Edit book has various tools to help with common tasks. These are accessed "
"via the :guilabel:`Tools` menu."
msgstr ""

# 2d5c4bfa3e1d4669b95892adad42417a
#: ../../home/kovid/work/calibre/manual/edit.rst:254
msgid "Edit the Table of Contents"
msgstr "Editer la Table des Matières"

# 24fb5c4ebc394951af08761c8a0933b4
#: ../../home/kovid/work/calibre/manual/edit.rst:256
msgid ""
"There is a dedicated tool to ease editing of the Table of Contents. Launch "
"it with :guilabel:`Tools->Table of Contents->Edit Table of Contents`."
msgstr ""

# 4416761c1c31483c9383be0dd1900919
#: ../../home/kovid/work/calibre/manual/edit.rst:263
msgid ""
"The Edit Table of Contents tool shows you the current Table of Contents (if "
"any) on the left. Simply double click on any entry to change its text. You "
"can also re-arrange entries by drag and drop or by using the buttons to the "
"right."
msgstr ""

# 9864aa7f7aaa49f583b028fd33b70201
#: ../../home/kovid/work/calibre/manual/edit.rst:267
msgid ""
"For books that do not have a pre-existing Table of Contents, the tool gives "
"you various options to auto-generate a Table of Contents from the text. You "
"can generate from the headings in the document, from links, from individual "
"files and so on."
msgstr ""

# 64556c5347414904b5ad656b7ad15cfd
#: ../../home/kovid/work/calibre/manual/edit.rst:272
msgid ""
"You can edit individual entries by clicking on them and then clicking the "
":guilabel:`Change the location this entry points to` button. This will open "
"up a mini-preview of the book, simply move the mouse cursor over the book "
"view panel, and click where you want the entry to point to. A thick green "
"line will show you the location. Click OK once you are happy with the "
"location."
msgstr ""

# e0fbb175cb834c919f15256c8f1eeb5e
#: ../../home/kovid/work/calibre/manual/edit.rst:283
msgid "Check Book"
msgstr "Vérifier le livre"

# 438128f12d5642aaa8be81c98e7548f1
#: ../../home/kovid/work/calibre/manual/edit.rst:285
msgid ""
"The :guilabel:`Check Book` tool searches your book for problems that could "
"prevent it working as intended on actual reader devices. Activate it via "
":guilabel:`Tools->Check Book`."
msgstr ""

# 6b4a100bc6a14a0b8adebc9b80876d3b
#: ../../home/kovid/work/calibre/manual/edit.rst:293
msgid ""
"Any problems found are reported in a nice, easy to use list. Clicking any "
"entry in the list shows you some help about that error as well as giving you"
" the option to auto-fix that error, if the error can be fixed automatically."
" You can also double click the error to open the location of the error in an"
" editor, so you can fix it yourself."
msgstr ""

# 180f8f24085242a4bc01a2d5c248053c
#: ../../home/kovid/work/calibre/manual/edit.rst:300
msgid "Some of the checks performed are:"
msgstr "Certains des contrôles exécutés sont : "

# 3eb4d347034a43f282e1414f42505820
#: ../../home/kovid/work/calibre/manual/edit.rst:302
msgid ""
"Malformed HTML markup. Any HTML markup that does not parse as well-formed "
"XML is reported. Correcting it will ensure that your markup works as "
"intended in all contexts. |app| can also auto-fix these errors, but auto-"
"fixing can sometimes have unexpected effects, so use with care. As always, a"
" checkpoint is created before auto-fixing so you can easily revert all "
"changes. Auto-fixing works by parsing the markup using the HTML 5 algorithm,"
" which is highly fault tolerant and then converting to well formed XML."
msgstr ""

# 83d554e7061b46a1b28dfd93d91c1791
#: ../../home/kovid/work/calibre/manual/edit.rst:311
msgid ""
"Malformed or unknown CSS styles. Any CSS that is not valid or that has "
"properties not defined in the CSS 2.1 standard (plus a few from CSS 3) are "
"reported. CSS is checked in all stylesheets, inline style attributes and "
"<style> tags in HTML files."
msgstr ""

# 224ed858feb64629be122d29128c2f60
#: ../../home/kovid/work/calibre/manual/edit.rst:316
msgid ""
"Broken links. Links that point to files inside the book that are missing are"
" reported."
msgstr ""

# c88c760e84ee479e827dc569cf838a76
#: ../../home/kovid/work/calibre/manual/edit.rst:319
msgid ""
"Unreferenced files. Files in the book that are not referenced by any other "
"file or are not in the spine are reported."
msgstr ""

# ae71279bd7fb4a109279d46239de648c
#: ../../home/kovid/work/calibre/manual/edit.rst:322
msgid ""
"Various common problems in OPF files such as duplicate spine or manifest "
"items, broken idrefs or meta cover tags, missing required sections and so "
"on."
msgstr ""

# d89ccbac58d84cf5bf70790432d69154
#: ../../home/kovid/work/calibre/manual/edit.rst:326
msgid ""
"Various compatibility checks for known problems that can cause the book to "
"malfunction on reader devices."
msgstr ""

# f41835193d5d420ab54d9e68b84a0ce2
#: ../../home/kovid/work/calibre/manual/edit.rst:330
msgid "Add a cover"
msgstr "Ajouter une couverture"

# 2a44c776158f4d2daaf7b01108711384
#: ../../home/kovid/work/calibre/manual/edit.rst:332
msgid ""
"You can easily add a cover to the book via :guilabel:`Tools->Add cover`. "
"This allows you to either choose an existing image in the book as the cover "
"or import a new image into the book and make it the cover. When editing EPUB"
" files, the HTML wrapper for the cover is automatically generated. If an "
"existing cover in the book is found, it is replaced. The tool also "
"automatically takes care of correctly marking the cover files as covers in "
"the OPF."
msgstr ""

# 5acd2b1df59e4cea9e84e0abcf1c8b3f
#: ../../home/kovid/work/calibre/manual/edit.rst:341
msgid "Embedding referenced fonts"
msgstr "Intégration des polices utilisées"

# 793728f468ea4a3e9b6cc1b36868284f
#: ../../home/kovid/work/calibre/manual/edit.rst:343
msgid ""
"Accessed via :guilabel:`Tools->Embed reference fonts`, this tool finds all "
"fonts referenced in the book and if they are not already embedded, searches "
"your computer for them and embeds them into the book, if found. Please make "
"sure that you have the necessary copyrights for embedding commercially "
"licensed fonts, before doing this."
msgstr ""

# 187fbe00458845819ea9ee18ea7a7968
#: ../../home/kovid/work/calibre/manual/edit.rst:350
msgid "Subsetting embedded fonts"
msgstr "Créer un sous-ensemble de polices"

# 11adddafc54d41beb35cd47d05b53e39
#: ../../home/kovid/work/calibre/manual/edit.rst:352
msgid ""
"Accessed via :guilabel:`Tools->Subset embedded fonts`, this tool reduces all"
" the fonts in the book to only contain glyphs for the text actually present "
"in the book. This commonly reduces the size of the font files by ~ 50%. "
"However, be aware that once the fonts are subset, if you add new text whose "
"characters are not previously present in the subset font, the font will not "
"work for the new text. So do this only as the last step in your workflow."
msgstr ""

# 6c5e66531b5f46a2add4cae23f4c557f
#: ../../home/kovid/work/calibre/manual/edit.rst:360
msgid "Smartening punctuation"
msgstr "Amélioration de la ponctuation"

# ee4b65f83ea74503b9ec97df8ffd02f8
#: ../../home/kovid/work/calibre/manual/edit.rst:362
msgid ""
"Convert plain text dashes, ellipsis, quotes, multiple hyphens, etc. into "
"their typographically correct equivalents. Note that the algorithm can "
"sometimes generate incorrect results, especially when single quotes at the "
"start of contractions are involved. Accessed via :guilabel:`Tools->Smarten "
"punctuation`."
msgstr ""

# 3f208925682b491fbfadfba4bc68538a
#: ../../home/kovid/work/calibre/manual/edit.rst:369
msgid "Removing unused CSS rules"
msgstr "Suppression en cours des règles CSS inutilisées"

# bbe2bccbe4124f6b91115fcb57d258df
#: ../../home/kovid/work/calibre/manual/edit.rst:371
msgid ""
"Remove all unused CSS rules from stylesheets and <style> tags. Some books "
"created from production templates can have a large number of extra CSS rules"
" that dont match any actual content. These extra rules can slow down readers"
" that need to process them all. Accessed via :guilabel:`Tools->Remove unused"
" CSS`."
msgstr ""

# 312686752c4f46d9b2702be4408eb51f
#: ../../home/kovid/work/calibre/manual/edit.rst:378
msgid "Fix HTML"
msgstr "Réparer l'HTML"

# 587570076f244ed490276ad040b0e710
#: ../../home/kovid/work/calibre/manual/edit.rst:380
msgid ""
"This tool simply converts HTML that cannot be parsed as XML into well-formed"
" XML. It is very common in ebooks to have non-well-formed XML, so this tool "
"simply automates the process of fixing such HTML. The tool works by parsing "
"the HTML using the HTML 5 algorithm (the algorithm used in all modern "
"browsers) and then converting the result into XML. Be aware that auto-fixing"
" can sometimes have counter-intuitive results. If you prefer, you can use "
"the Check Book tool discussed above to find and manually correct problems in"
" the HTML. Accessed via :guilabel:`Tools->Fix HTML`."
msgstr ""

# 01d9f1b1dff4482f92ea87107016a165
#: ../../home/kovid/work/calibre/manual/edit.rst:390
msgid "Beautifying files"
msgstr "Embellissement des fichiers"

# 81c11d3970834a9991addfa7c5edf344
#: ../../home/kovid/work/calibre/manual/edit.rst:392
msgid ""
"This tool is used to auto-format all HTML and CSS files so that they \"look "
"pretty\". The code is auto-indented so that it lines up nicely, blank lines "
"are inserted where appropriate and so on. Note that beautifying also auto-"
"fixes broken HTML/CSS. Therefore, if you dont want any auto-fixing to be "
"performed, first use the Check Book tool to correct all problems and only "
"then run beautify.  Accessed via :guilabel:`Tools->Beautify all files`."
msgstr ""

# 20ebebcf35c641659d2779d44d4a84b7
#: ../../home/kovid/work/calibre/manual/edit.rst:400
msgid ""
"In HTML any text can have significant whitespace, via the CSS white-space "
"directive. Therefore, beautification could potentially change the rendering "
"of the HTML. To avoid this as far as possible, the beautify algorithm only "
"beautifies block level tags that contain other block level tags. So, for "
"example, text inside a <p> tag will not have its whitespace changed. But a "
"<body> tag that contains only other <p> and <div> tags will be beautified.  "
"This can sometimes mean that a particular file will not be affected by "
"beautify as it has no suitable block level tags. In such cases you can try "
"different beautification tools, that are less careful, for example: `HTML "
"Tidy <http://infohound.net/tidy/>`_."
msgstr ""

# e4776772ea8b4c5eb22cc53d423efde7
#: ../../home/kovid/work/calibre/manual/edit.rst:413
msgid "Insert inline Table of Contents"
msgstr "Insère une Table des Matières"

# ec252dca370143c69ebe65278fc88a73
#: ../../home/kovid/work/calibre/manual/edit.rst:415
msgid ""
"Normally in ebooks, the Table of Contents is separate from the main text and"
" is typically accessed via a special Table of Contents button/menu in the "
"ebook reading device. You can also have |app| automatically generate an "
"*inline* Table of Contents that becomes part of the text of the book. It is "
"generated based on the currently defined Table of Contents."
msgstr ""

# ffc33535bc3541249a1646db73ddad13
#: ../../home/kovid/work/calibre/manual/edit.rst:421
msgid ""
"If you use this tool multiple times, each invocation will cause the "
"previously created inline Table of Contents to be replaced. The tool can be "
"accessed via :guilabel:`Tools->Table of Contents->Insert inline Table of "
"Contents`."
msgstr ""

# 32d710e4944e4204866cebe3dbbc708a
#: ../../home/kovid/work/calibre/manual/edit.rst:426
msgid "Set Semantics"
msgstr "Paramétre Sémantique"

# 6cbf518ac05e4ecbaa0f3281c388cfc6
#: ../../home/kovid/work/calibre/manual/edit.rst:428
msgid ""
"This tool is used to set *semantics* in EPUB files. Semantics are simply, "
"links in the OPF file that identify certain locations in the book as having "
"special meaning. You can use them to identify the foreword, dedication, "
"cover, table of contents, etc. Simply choose the type of semantic "
"information you want to specify and then select the location in the book the"
" link should point to. This tool can be accessed via :guilabel:`Tools->Set "
"semantics`."
msgstr ""

# 8ddd34bd2c4b456985ea9d43814a7a3c
#: ../../home/kovid/work/calibre/manual/edit.rst:436
msgid "Filter style information"
msgstr "Filtrer l'information de style"

# 2e48fb58cd5f47e6a648ad3a0c6610a9
#: ../../home/kovid/work/calibre/manual/edit.rst:438
msgid ""
"This tool can be used to easily remove specified CSS style properties from "
"the entire book. You can tell it what properties you want removed, for "
"example, ``color, background-color, line-height`` and it will remove them "
"from everywhere they occur --- stylesheets, ``<style>`` tags and inline "
"``style`` attributes. After removing the style information, a summary of all"
" the changes made is displayed so you can see exactly what was changed. The "
"tool can be accessed via :guilabel:`Tools->Filter style information`."
msgstr ""

# 6ce9704063544eeea72827f01d2d6435
#: ../../home/kovid/work/calibre/manual/edit.rst:449
msgid "Checkpoints"
msgstr "Points de contrôle"

# b92c01c0b3ff4d3fadd0bab08d2c1517
#: ../../home/kovid/work/calibre/manual/edit.rst:451
msgid ""
":guilabel:`Checkpoints` are a way to mark the current state of the book as "
"\"special\". You can then go on to do whatever changes you want to the book "
"and if you dont like the results, return to the checkpointed state. "
"Checkpoints are automatically created every time you run any of the "
"automated tools described in the previous section."
msgstr ""

# 8d816dcec6054e2f9f9e08b739fd66d7
#: ../../home/kovid/work/calibre/manual/edit.rst:457
msgid ""
"You can create a checkpoint via :guilabel:`Edit->Create checkpoint`. And go "
"back to a previous checkpoint with :guilabel:`Edit->Revert to ...`"
msgstr ""

# 920cc39fcd2e438ba09c246658d8de0d
#: ../../home/kovid/work/calibre/manual/edit.rst:460
msgid ""
"The checkpointing functionality is in addition to the normal Undo/redo "
"mechanism when editing individual files. Checkpoints are particularly useful"
" for when changes are spread over multiple files in the book or when you "
"wish to be able to revert a large group of related changes as a whole."
msgstr ""

# f663662c990d4276b87318b29e57b9d1
#: ../../home/kovid/work/calibre/manual/edit.rst:465
msgid ""
"You can see a list of available checkpoints via "
":guilabel:`View->Checkpoints`. You can compare the current state of the book"
" to a specified checkpoint using the :ref:`diff` tool -- by selecting the "
"checkpoint of interest and clicking the :guilabel:`Compare` button. The "
":guilabel:`Revert to` button restores the book to the selected checkpoint, "
"undoing all changes since that checkpoint was created."
msgstr ""

# 1600f245f6954d3d8279deb5cc108ba4
#: ../../home/kovid/work/calibre/manual/edit.rst:473
msgid "The Live Preview panel"
msgstr "Le Panneau de Prévisualisation Directe"

# c56af17919bd40f1b7e4b9406c33a205
#: ../../home/kovid/work/calibre/manual/edit.rst:479
msgid ""
"The :guilabel:`File Preview` gives you an overview of the various files "
"inside The live preview panel shows you the changes you are making live "
"(with a second or two of delay). As you edit HTML or CSS files, the preview "
"panel is updated automatically to reflect your changes. As you move the "
"cursor around in the editor, the preview panel will track its location, "
"showing you the corresponding location in the book. Clicking in the preview "
"panel, will cause the cursor in the editor to be positioned over the element"
" you clicked. If you click a link pointing to another file in the book, that"
" file will be opened in the edit and the preview panel, automatically."
msgstr ""

# c8cdb2b55def4c9aa3bfbee7e9223013
#: ../../home/kovid/work/calibre/manual/edit.rst:489
msgid ""
"You can turn off the automatic syncing of position and live preview of "
"changes -- by buttons under the preview panel. The live update of the "
"preview panel only happens when you are not actively typing in the editor, "
"so as not to be distracting or slow you down, waiting for the preview to "
"render."
msgstr ""

# cff27ecd43664f4390733d841d73d12a
#: ../../home/kovid/work/calibre/manual/edit.rst:494
msgid ""
"The preview panel shows you how the text will look when viewed. However, the"
" preview panel is not a substitute for actually testing your book an actual "
"reader device. It is both more, and less capable than an actual reader. It "
"will tolerate errors and sloppy markup much better than most reader devices."
" It will also not show you page margins, page breaks and embedded fonts that"
" use font name aliasing. Use the preview panel while you are working on the "
"book, but once you are done, review it in an actual reader device or "
"software emulator."
msgstr ""

# 1b64bdf4ec8246f2b5e6c77a60185bcd
#: ../../home/kovid/work/calibre/manual/edit.rst:503
msgid ""
"The preview panel does not support embedded fonts if the name of the font "
"inside the font file does not match the name in the CSS @font-face rule. You"
" can use the Check Book tool to quickly find and fix any such problem fonts."
msgstr ""

# c826ddde29d94c958e44ac9f37ae5d73
#: ../../home/kovid/work/calibre/manual/edit.rst:509
msgid "Splitting HTML files"
msgstr "Fractionnement des fichiers HTML"

# fbdb65d0dae847c5ab95346ba8679071
#: ../../home/kovid/work/calibre/manual/edit.rst:513
msgid ""
"One, perhaps non-obvious, use of the preview panel is to split long HTML "
"files. While viewing the file you want to split, click the :guilabel:`split "
"mode` button under the preview panel |spmb|. Then simply move your mouse to "
"the place where you want to split the file and click. A thick green line "
"will show you exactly where the split will happen as you move your mouse. "
"Once you have found the location you want, simply click and the split will "
"be performed."
msgstr ""

# b927bc2af49f4618af468004484b5896
#: ../../home/kovid/work/calibre/manual/edit.rst:520
msgid ""
"Splitting the file will automatically update all links and references that "
"pointed into the bottom half of the file and will open the newly split file "
"in an editor."
msgstr ""

# 0196e7edb08740239745f2dbcf98ff72
#: ../../home/kovid/work/calibre/manual/edit.rst:524
msgid ""
"You can also split a single HTML file at multiple locations automatically, "
"by right clicking inside the file in the editor and choosing "
":guilabel:`Split at multiple locations`. This will allow you to easily split"
" a large file at all heading tags or all tags having a certain class and so "
"on."
msgstr ""

# da1796df5d9d4dd88b72a46f67c11c5d
#: ../../home/kovid/work/calibre/manual/edit.rst:534
msgid "The Live CSS panel"
msgstr "Le panneau CCS en temps réel"

# 16b0c955ee7a4ad89489b48c44db58a4
#: ../../home/kovid/work/calibre/manual/edit.rst:541
msgid ""
"The :guilabel:`Live CSS` panel shows you all the style rules that apply to "
"the tag you are currently editing. The name of tag, along with its line "
"number in the editor are displayed, followed by a list of matching style "
"rules."
msgstr ""

# 297f45d62c7a4c8b8c0bd5fd140be9c8
#: ../../home/kovid/work/calibre/manual/edit.rst:545
msgid ""
"It is a great way to quickly see which style rules apply to any tag. The "
"view also has clickable links (in blue), which take you directly to the "
"location where the style was defined, in case you wish to make any changes "
"to the style rules. Style rules that apply directly to the tag, as well as "
"rules that are inherited from parent tags are shown."
msgstr ""

# 021b3476c64e43c787361c8e7140047a
#: ../../home/kovid/work/calibre/manual/edit.rst:551
msgid ""
"The panel also shows you what the finally calculated styles for the tag are."
" Properties in the list that are superseded by higher priority rules are "
"shown with a line through them."
msgstr ""

# a939d98a1ea44420a07d1e3e2d5139dd
#: ../../home/kovid/work/calibre/manual/edit.rst:555
msgid "You can enable the Live CSS panel via :guilabel:`View->Live CSS`."
msgstr ""

# c7ca0de12620426db931c015d4b60126
#: ../../home/kovid/work/calibre/manual/edit.rst:562
msgid "Miscellaneous Tools"
msgstr "Outils divers"

# ea684f15d8734f4181e2a840835cabf7
#: ../../home/kovid/work/calibre/manual/edit.rst:564
